; block.m9s
; M9 Custom Character Example Program
; This program demonstrates several key techniques:
;
;   1. Duplicating the default character set (charset)
;   2. Modifying individual character glyphs
;   3. Updating memory location pointers
;   4. Implementing input waiting loops
;
; Specific actions performed:
;   - Replaces the exclamation point glyph with a solid 5x5 square
;   - Places the modified "!" character at the top-left of the LORES text buffer
;   - Displays the result as a green 5x5 pixel block
;   - Enters a loop waiting for the FIRE1 button press

